cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL

The paper deals with action recognition in videos, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). It also discusses the use of webly supervised learning, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). The dataset is collected from YouTube, which is a multimedia platform (cs.MM) and the paper proposes a semantical hierarchical structure for the mined classes, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper does not explicitly mention any other sub-categories, but these five are the most likely based on the content of the paper.
